Description: Fragment of oval handle of a Rhodian pottery pottery transport amphora. Worn. Clay fine rose-buff. Circular stamp with Helios head symbol. Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 134, 9. Name Klenostratos. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0165.19. Only one secondary stamp with Klenostratos is cited by M. Palaczyk, 'Die Zusatzstempel ('secondary stamps') der rhodischen Amphoren', ÖJh 68 (1999) 78; eight are cited by Senol 2016.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1125)
